name: sa4_i05a_type_edu_inst_att_by_i_status_by_sex_census_2016
title: SA4-I05a Type of Educational Institute Attending by Indigenous Status by sex-Census 2016

legal.licenceType: Creative Commons Attribution 2.5 Australia (CC BY 2.5 AU)

keyword: atsip,aboriginal torres strait islander peoples,i05a,census,2016,indigenous status,sex,education,students,educational institution
abstract:
SA4 based data for Type of Educational Institution Attending (Full/Part Time Students Status by Age) by Indigenous Status by Sex, in Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People Profile (ATSIP), 2016 Census. Count of persons attending an educational institution. I05 is broken up into two sections (I05a and I05b), this section covers ?Pre-school Aboriginal and or Torres Strait Islander Males? - ?Type of educational institution not stated Indigenous status not stated Females?. The data is by SA4 2016 boundaries. Periodicity: 5-Yearly.
Note: There are small random adjustments made to all cell values to protect the confidentiality of data. These adjustments may cause the sum of rows or columns to differ by small amounts from table totals.
For more information visit the data source: http://www.abs.gov.au/census.
